05/04/2007
SPLIT, Croatia -- Police detained 40 football fans who went on a rampage Wednesday (April 4th) ahead of a match between local clubs Dinamo Zagreb and Hajduk Split. 
Police say the rioters -- supporters of Dinamo Zagreb -- were arrested after they destroyed parked vehicles early in the morning after arriving aboard the night train from Zagreb. 
Police seized baseball bats and flares. 
(HRT, Index.hr, CNN - 04/04/07)
